article.description: Robert Morris hits buzzer-beater, beats CCSU 53-52
article.headline: Robert Morris hits buzzer-beater, beats CCSU 53-52
article.linkText: Robert Morris hits buzzer-beater, beats CCSU 53-52
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Aaron Tate put up a buzzer-beating tip-in to secure Robert Morris' 53-52 come-from-behind victory over Central Connecticut State on Saturday. Robert Morris trailed throughout the second half but a 5:42 cold spell by CCSU put the Colonials within striking distance. Rodney Pryor made a trey and Marcquise Reed hit a jumper for a one-point game with two minutes remaining. Robert Morris then turned the ball over on back-to-back possessions, but the Blue Devils missed all four of their shot attempts. The Colonials took possession with 16 seconds left -- Reed tried a jumper that didn't drop, and Tate's tip-in bounced around the rim before falling for the win. Tate finished with four points and six rebounds. Reed scored 18 points for the Colonials (13-13, 9-5), who hold sole possession of third place in the Northeast Conference. Matt Mobley led the Blue Devils (3-24, 1-13) with 23 points.
